node.text:
We're kicking off our first est film production with a momentous Malvern Home renovation by @dohertydesignstudio from est magazine issue #35.
.
Tapping into its rich architectural past and 1980s new wave bones, @dohertydesignstudio have skilfully commandeered an epic journey to reinvent this Melbourne family home. An original 1980's design by architect Peter McIntyre. .
.
Experience the entire home via the link in profile or read the full feature in est magazine issue #35. .
.
Design @dohertydesignstudio
Building design @arialexander
Builder @north_building_group 
Styling @heathernetteking 
Florals and assitant styling @rachelpolivkastylist 
Art consultant @gb.art.consulting 
Landscape design @benscott_design 
Videography @richardlipp.studio
Words @meganmayrawson
Art @tompolo @liamsnootle @anyapesce @oocaleb @davidjamesgriggs @christianthompsonartist #leekyoung-hwa 
Furniture & Objects @domoaustralia @lightlydesign @loomtowels @fenton_and_fenton @abode_living @moderntimesau @ajarfurniture @lamarzoccohomeau

node.text:
Great land. Great architecture. Great living. In an est exclusive, we feature three unique films by Rob Mills Architecture & Interiors (RMA). Australian-based RMA’s latest project, a ground-breaking residence in Byron Bay incorporates Mill’s signature use of drama, curves, lines, light and a reflection of the qualities of the land.
.
View all three films via link in profile.
.
Videography @collider__
Creative Direction | Design @robmillsarchitects

node.text:
ARCHITECTURE | House in Monsaraz 
​.
Lisbon studio @_airesmateus designed 'House in Monsaraz' to ​embrace views over ​Alqueva Lake, Portugal while appearing as part of the landscape. 
​.
The sculptural concrete home has been carved into the hillside – leaving only one side of the roof visible – ​with a protected courtyard at its core. 
​.
​Design @_airesmateus
​Photography @oruicardoso and @jgphoto.graphy
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/

node.text:
HOME TOUR | Ballarat House
​.
@kennedy_nolan's rendition of a family home in Ballarat, Victoria epitomises comfort and warmth in a lakeside setting. 
​.
The studio wanted to pivot away from some of the more ‘grandiose’ houses along Ballarat’s lakefront, drawing them towards the cosy and nostalgic 70s-inspired style that the home embodies. 
​.
​See the entire home on est – link in profile. 
​.
​Design @kennedy_nolan
​Photography @derek_swalwell
​Words @hollybeadle

node.text:
FEATURED HOME | A New Order
​.
A Californian family home renovated in the late 1990s felt disconnected from its facade
before designer @mandy.graham’s intervention, which saw her take an equally refined and restrained approach to transforming each space. 
​.
​A reinterpretation of an existing boxy narrative has resulted in a home that now reflects features of postmodernism through large blocks of stone, softened by a signature arch motif.
​.
​Read more about this Californian home inside the latest issue of est Magazine for free – link in profile. 
​.
​Design @mandy.graham
​Photography @manololangis
​Words @lidiaboniwell_
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/magazine/est-magazine-issue-41/

STRAIGHT FROM THE HEART | Richard Christiansen
​.
"It sounds cheesy, but I think Mother Nature is the greatest creative teacher. My office, which opens up to the garden, is where I work all day long for both of my businesses. Quite selfishly, the different structures at Flamingo Estate were built to work in the garden and work in nature. I’ve often said that the most beautiful room in the house is the garden, influencing colour, texture and form."
​– Richard Christiansen

node.text:
HOME TOUR | 8 Yard House
​.
Unlike most houses with a clear ‘front’ and a ‘back’, the 8 Yard House by @studio__bright offers a series of glimpses through a sequence of garden walls, offering what Mel refers to as ‘layered views’.
​.
​And while many architects see a newly completed house as ‘finished’, for Mel Bright, it’s the thought of what this house will look like in 10 years that excites her most, with the plants in the window boxes cascading down walls and trees creating an even more verdant and private oasis.
​.
​Read more about @studio__bright's award-winning home in North Fitzroy, Melbourne on estliving.com – link in profile. 
​.
